Technologists, doctors, accountants, psychologists, process engineers and tyrannical bosses all regularly apply some variant of the stressing principle. Does it bend or does it break? While an absence of pressure is to be desired and embraced, it tells one nothing about resilience. Until one loads extreme pressure on to a steel bar, or a financial institution, or a human heart, or a government, one knows next to nothing about its real strength. Not since 1939 has the world been put to such an extreme test as Covid-19. There have been unexpected failures and surprising successes. France, Italy and Spain regularly...